  "title": "Administrative Assistant (Project Admin)",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a highly organised and proactive Administrative Assistant to provide dedicated support to our IWMF Project team. You will be the operational backbone of the project, ensuring smooth day-to-day administration, seamless communication, and impeccable documentation. <br /></p><p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li>Create, format, edit, and proofread project documents, including plans, reports.</li><li>Maintain and organise all projects files (digital and physical) in accordance with company and project governance standards.</li><li>Assist in the preparation of regular status reports and dashboards by collecting and compiling data from team members.</li><li>Manage document control processes, including versioning, distribution, and archiving.</li><li>Perform general administrative duties such as copying, scanning, and mailing.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications & Skills</strong><br /></p><ul><li>Proven experience (2+ years) as an Administrative Assistant, Executive Assistant, or Project Coordinator.</li><li>Exceptional proficiency in the Microsoft Office Suite (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook) and Adobe Acrobat.</li><li>Good written and verbal communication.</li><li>Outstanding organisational and time-management abilities with a keen attention to detail.</li><li>Ability to handle confidential information with discretion.</li><li>Proactive problem-solver who can work independently and anticipate needs.</li><li>Team-oriented with a positive, collaborative attitude.</li><li>Business Administration Degree or equivalent relevant experience required.</li></ul><p></p><h3></h3>",
